<a name="sending"></a>
<h4>Sending invitations</h4>

<p>Enter the name of the firm you want to invite and the email address of the compensation specialist. If the firm is
already a CompSage member, entering the email address is not necessary; you will receive a prompt to invite the firm
after entering its name. If the firm is not a member and you do not know the compensation specialist's email address,
you will need to contact the firm to get that information.</p>

<p>If you are a member of any networks, the networks will be listed on the left of the invitation page. You can invite
all members of a network by clicking on the '+' button next to the network name.</p>

<p>Invitations will be delivered via email once you submit your billing information. You may enter a custom invitation
message that will be included in the invitation email by clicking on 'Set a Custom Invitation Message'.</p>

<p>You are required to invite at least five firms to your survey.</p>

<a name="previewing"></a>
<h4>Previewing survey questions</h4>

<p>This is how your survey will be presented to participants. Verify the questions are worded as you want them, are in
the desired order, and have the appropriate response types. You may still edit the questions after the survey is
created, but changes cannot be made once survey responses have been collected.</p>

<a name="billing"></a>
<h4>Billing</h4>

<p>You can select to be billed via credit card or by invoice. If you select to be billed via credit card, you card will
be charged upon successful completion of the survey and and a receipt will be delivered via email. If you select to be
billed via invoice, you will receive an invoice via email upon successful completion of the survey.</p>

<a name="status"></a>
<h4>Survey status</h4>

<p>All of the surveys you are sponsoring will be listed under the 'My Surveys' section of the 'Surveys &amp; Results'
tab. The status of the survey is listed below the job title.</p>

<p><b>Running:</b> The survey is in progress. The number of participants and the time until the deadline are displayed with the
status. Click on the job title to edit the survey details, respond to the survey, or invite additional firms to
participate in the survey.</p>

<p><b>Stalled:</b> The survey deadline has passed, but the survey did not have at least five firms participate or not all
questions received enough responses to report data. Click on the job title to fix the error. Cancel the survey to remove
the survey and notify participants that results will not be available. Extend the survey deadline and invite additional
firms to increase participation. Or, if at least one question has enough responses to report results, finish the partial
survey. Questions that did not receive enough responses will be excluded from the report.</p>

<p><b>Expired:</b> The survey is over three weeks old and never completed successfully. Click on the job title to cancel the
survey.</p>

<p><b>Billing Error:</b> We were unable to successfully bill your credit card. Please contact us as soon as possible to resolve
the billing problems so results can be made available to you and the survey participants.</p>

<p><b>Finished:</b> Finished surveys are listed under the 'Recent Survey Results' section.</p>

<h3>Networks</h3>

<a name="creating"></a>
<h4>Creating a network</h4>

<p>Click on the "Create a New Network" link at the top of the Networks &amp; Contacts page. Choose a name that concisely
describes the types of firms you will be inviting to the network. For example, if you are planning to create a network
consisting of large healthcare firms serving the Minneapolis metro area, you could name the network "Large Healthcare
Firms, Minneapolis Metro Area". Use the optional network description to provide additional details about the network and
its purpose. Click the 'create' button to create the network.</p>

<p>Once you have created the network, you can invite other firms to join. For each firm, enter their name and email
address in the 'New Invitation' form and click 'Add'. The firm will be notified of the invitation by email. Note that
the invited firms do not become members of the network until they have accepted the invitation. When a firm has joined
the network, you will see their name listed in the 'Network Members' section.</p>

<p>As the creator of the network, you are both the manager and a member of the network. You may go back at any time and
invite additional firms to the network. You may also change the network name and description at any time by following
the 'Edit Network' link in the 'Network Activities' section.</p>

<a name="joining"></a>
<h4>Joining a network</h4>

<p>To join a network you must first be invited by the network manager. Once invited, you will receive an email
notification containing a link for you to join the network. Your network invitations will also be visible on the
Networks &amp; Contacts page. If you do not wish to join a network to which you are invited, you may decline the
invitation from the Networks &amp; Contacts page.</p</h4>

<a name="leaving"></a>
<h4>Leaving a network</h4>

<p>You may leave the network by clicking the 'Leave Network' link in the 'Network Activities' section. If you leave a
network in which you are the only member, the network will be deleted.</p>

<a name="removing"></a>
<h4>Removing members from a network</h4>

<p>In order to remove firms from a network, you must be the network manager. To remove a firm, go to the network page
and click on the remove link next to the name of the member you wish to remove.</p>

<a name="changing"></a>
<h4>Changing the network manager</h4>

<p>Follow the 'Edit Network' link in the 'Network Activities' section. Click on 'Change network manager' and select one
of the firms from the list and click the 'Update' button.</p>

<h3>Accounts</h3>

<a name="closing"></a>
<h4>Closing your account</h4>

<p>Please contact us if you wish to close your account.</p>

<a name="updating"></a>
<h4>Updating your account</h4>

<p>Log in and click on the 'Account Settings' link at the top right of the page. Make updates to any of the fields you
wish to change. Once you are satisfied with the changes, click the 'Update' button. Note that if you change your email
address, you will need to use the updated email address when logging in. If you wish to change the name of your firm,
please contact us.</p>

<a name="password"></a>
<h4>Changing your password</h4>

<p>Log in and click on the 'Account Settings' link at the top right. Click on the 'Change My Password' link at the
bottom of the form and enter the new password. Click the update button to save your changes.</p>
